&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>PowerDNS is (as its name suggests) a DNS server. It&amp;rsquo;s a direct competitor to Bind. It aims to be less RAM-intensive and offers more flexible configuration options than Bind.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Apt-cacher-ng: Setting Up a Proxy for APT</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/apt-cacher-ng-mise-en-place-d-un-proxy-pour-apt/</link><pubDate>Tue, 31 Aug 2010 07:51:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/apt-cacher-ng-mise-en-place-d-un-proxy-pour-apt/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Without having an amazing internet connection and using virtual machines, it quickly becomes tedious to wait ages to download the same packages for all these VMs. So I looked for a solution to have a kind of cache specifically for apt.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I found happiness with apt-cacher-ng which, from what I&amp;rsquo;ve read, is the most complete solution available today.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="installation">Installation &lt;a href="#installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>As usual, it&amp;rsquo;s simple:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="0cea20d" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>aptitude install apt-cacher-ng&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;p>My server has the IP &lt;strong>192.168.100.1&lt;/strong>. If you want to modify some small options, I invite you to look at the file &lt;code>/etc/apt-cacher-ng/acng.conf&lt;/code>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>